---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { blogPosts } from '../../data/blog-posts';

const posts = blogPosts;
---

<Layout
  title="Percentage Math — Guides & Explainers"
  description="Plain-English guides on percentage calculations, discounts, percentage change, tip math, and everyday numbers — from CalPercentage.com."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 py-10 sm:py-16">

    <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-muted mb-5 font-mono">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-ink no-underline transition-colors">Home</a>
      <span>/</span>
      <span class="text-ink">Blog</span>
    </nav>

    <p class="form-label mb-2">Blog</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.05em; line-height:1.1;">
      Guides &amp; explainers
    </h1>
    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-7 mb-8 max-w-xl">
      Plain-English breakdowns of percentage math — discounts, sale prices, percentage change, and the calculations behind everyday numbers.
    </p>

    <!-- Articles -->
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-14" style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-line); padding-top:2rem;">
      {posts.map(post => (
        <a href={post.href} class="card flex flex-col gap-1 no-underline hover:shadow-[0_0_0_1.5px_var(--color-ink)]">
          <p class="text-xs text-muted font-mono">{post.date}</p>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink" style="letter-spacing:-0.02em;">{post.title}</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-5">{post.desc}</p>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- Editorial content for SEO/GEO -->
    <div class="prose-section space-y-10" style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-line); padding-top:2.5rem;">

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.03em;">What this blog covers</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 mb-4">
          Percentage math shows up everywhere — a landlord raising your rent by 8%, a store advertising 30% off, a stock that dropped 12% last week, or a restaurant bill where you want to leave a fair tip. The calculations are simple once you know the formula, but most people were never taught them clearly in school.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7">
          This blog fills that gap. Each guide here focuses on one real-world percentage problem, explains the formula in plain English, walks through worked examples with actual numbers, and points you to the right <a href="/" class="text-ink underline underline-offset-2">free calculator</a> to check your work. No textbook jargon, no unnecessary theory — just the math you actually need.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.03em;">Why percentage calculations matter in daily life</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 mb-4">
          Percentages are the language of change and comparison. When you see a price tag that says "20% off," you need to know what dollar amount that means before you can decide if the deal is worth it. When your salary goes from $55,000 to $58,000, you want to know whether that's a 5% raise or a 5.5% raise — especially if you're negotiating. When you're comparing two savings accounts at 4.1% and 4.35% APY, that seemingly small difference compounds into real money over time.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 mb-4">
          Beyond personal finance, percentages appear in health data (a medication that's 94% effective), statistics (a poll with a 3-point margin of error), nutrition labels (25% of your daily sodium), and business metrics (a 7% quarter-over-quarter revenue increase). Being comfortable with percentage math makes you a sharper reader of news, a smarter shopper, and a more confident decision-maker.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7">
          The guides on this blog are designed to give you that fluency quickly — without making you sit through a math class to get there.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.03em;">The core percentage formula — a quick refresher</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 mb-4">
          Almost every percentage problem is a variation of one formula: <strong class="text-ink">Percentage = (Part ÷ Whole) × 100</strong>. From this single equation, three questions can be answered:
        </p>
        <ol class="space-y-2 list-decimal list-inside text-sm text-secondary leading-7 mb-4">
          <li><strong class="text-ink">What is X% of Y?</strong> Multiply Y by (X ÷ 100). Example: 15% of $80 = $80 × 0.15 = $12.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">X is what percent of Y?</strong> Divide X by Y and multiply by 100. Example: $12 is what percent of $80? → (12 ÷ 80) × 100 = 15%.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">X is Y% of what?</strong> Divide X by (Y ÷ 100). Example: $12 is 15% of what? → 12 ÷ 0.15 = $80.</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7">
          Percentage <em>change</em> adds one more layer: <strong class="text-ink">% Change = ((New − Old) ÷ Old) × 100</strong>. A positive result is an increase; a negative result is a decrease. Each article on this blog walks through one of these formulas with real examples so the pattern sticks.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3" style="letter-spacing:-0.03em;">Free calculators to go with these guides</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-7 mb-4">
          Every guide links to a matching calculator so you can apply the formula instantly without doing the arithmetic by hand. Here's what's available on CalPercentage:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-secondary leading-6">
          <li><a href="/percentage-calculator" class="text-ink underline underline-offset-2">Percentage Calculator</a> — solve all three types of percentage questions in one tool.</li>
          <li><a href="/percentage-of-number" class="text-ink underline underline-offset-2">Percentage of a Number</a> — find X% of any amount instantly.</li>
          <li><a href="/percentage-increase" class="text-ink underline underline-offset-2">Percentage Increase &amp; Decrease Calculator</a> — calculate the exact % change between two values.</li>
          <li><a href="/discount-calculator" class="text-ink underline underline-offset-2">Discount Calculator</a> — see the sale price and exact savings for any % off.</li>
          <li><a href="/tip-calculator" class="text-ink underline underline-offset-2">Tip Calculator</a> — split a bill and calculate tips at any percentage.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
